    • Method Detail

      • comesBefore

        public boolean comesBefore(AList<T> list,
                  int a,
                  int b)
        Compare two items in the given list for purposes of sorting. This determines the sorted order of the list items.

        The default implementation of this method casts each item to type Comparable<T>; calls the compareTo() method on the item at position a, passing the item at position b as the argument; and returns true if the compareTo() method returns a value less than 0. If this is not the desired behavior, or if the list items cannot be cast to type Comparable<T>, then override this method in a subclass.

        Parameters:
        list - List being sorted.
        a - Position of first list item being compared.
        b - Position of second list item being compared.
        Returns:
        True if the item at position a comes before the item at position b in the desired ordering, false otherwise.

      • swap

        protected void swap(AList<T> list,
        int a,
        int b)
        Swap two items in the given list for purposes of sorting.

        The default implementation calls list.swap(a,b). If this is not the desired behavior, then override this method in a subclass; for example, to swap the elements of other arrays or lists in addition to this list.

        Parameters:
        list - List being sorted.
        a - Position of first list item being swapped.
        b - Position of second list item being swapped.
